(1) There shall be a National Disaster Management Office which shall be responsible for the day-to-day operations of disaster management.
* The National Disaster Management Office shall consist of
	* the Director, the Principal Disaster Management Officer and the Senior Disaster Management Officer who shall be public officers appointed to those posts by the Council; and
	* other persons appointed and employed in accordance with the provisions of the Public Service Act.
	* The main functions of the National Disaster Management Office are to
	* implement polices laid down by the Council and Cabinet;
	* advise the National Disaster Controller, the Council and other relevant bodies on disaster related matters;
	* initiate formulation of policies for development of disaster management organizations and activities;
	* arrange meetings of the Council and its sub-committees, provide Secretariat support and initiate follow-up action;
	* deal with disaster management related issues at the national level;
	* initiate and co-ordinate the preparation for rehabilitation plans after national reviews;
	* review disaster preparedness arrangements and carry out post-disaster reviews;
	* co-ordinate disaster management training and public education; and
	* perform any other functions as directed by the National Disaster Controller.
	* co-ordinate activities of disaster monitoring, warning and immediate post-disaster response including disaster relief work;
	* be activated when a specific threat of disaster develops or when a disaster occurs;
	* be manned on a 24-hour basis from teams drawn from the public service and agencies when activated;
	* carry out its functions according to the Standard Operating Procedure;
	* obtain regular situation reports from the Divisional and District Emergency Operations Centres;
	* co-ordinate requests for assistance during emergency situations .

